    About

    Description

    Vincent Willem van Gogh was a Dutch Post-Impressionist painter who is among the most famous and influential figures in the history of Western art. In just over a decade, he created approximately 2100 artworks, including around 860 oil paintings, most of them in the last two years of his life. Wikipedia
    Born: March 30, 1853, Zundert, Netherlands
    Died: July 29, 1890 (age 37 years), Auvers-sur-Oise, France
    Periods: Post-Impressionism, Pointillism, Neo-Impressionism
    Influenced by: Claude Monet, Paul Czanne, Rembrandt, MORE
    On view: Van Gogh Museum, Krller-Mller Museum, MORE
    Parents: Anna Carbentus van Gogh, Theodorus van Gogh
